Participant List




View Sample Report






2017 Survey Pricing
Participant - C$3,600
Non-participant - C$10,800  

2017 Survey Schedule
Participation opens: Mar 21
Participation closes: May 19
Results available: Sep



. 
            


Mercer's Canada Investment Management Compensation Survey (CIMS) provides the Canadian financial services community with the most accurate compensation data for 103 industry positions. CIMS is supported by senior executives in the financial services industry. Along with that, this survey is sponsored by an industry advisor with support from survey partner Russell Reynolds.

Some of the positions included in this survey are client and portfolio managers, researchers, and economists and traders, as well as executive, finance, administration, operations, and sales and marketing roles.

Key data includes:

Addition of new roles, including Trader and Research positions defined by asset class, and Real Estate and Private Banking positions. 
 Defining performance measures and differentiated compensation programs for front office employees.
Participation submission growth to better enhance data refinement by sub-sector. 
Improved survey process with streamlining questions and simplifying submission requirements.
 Increased client engagement which leverages our market expertise and insights to help you use the survey results effectively. 










 
                                
